article.headline: Houston 75, Centenary 62
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Oliver Lafayette scored 21 points, including 5-of-6 from 3-point range, to lead Houston to a 75-62 win Tuesday night over Centenary. Lafayette, who came into the game averaging 20 points, caught fire late in the first half to help the Cougars (8-3) post a 44-33 halftime lead. Also in double figures for Houston was Ramon Dyer and Brian Latham, who each scored 15. Centenary (2-9) was led by Larry Logan's 14 points, while Xavier Burnette and Clarke Jackson each added 13. Houston's defense forced 25 Centenary turnovers, resulting in 36 points compared to 15 points off turnovers for the Gents.
